<div class="wpcf7-response-output wpcf7-display-none"></div></form></div><p class="txt-desc">By Clicking ``Sign-up Now`` you agree to our terms of conditions of this product.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-7 col-md-8 col-lg-7 col-lg-offset-1"><ul class="header-txt-list"><li><i class="fa fa-recycle"></i><h4>Art of reusability and recycling</h4><p>A zero waste based strategy that supports  goals of sustainability- economic well-being, environmental protection and social well-being</p></li><li><i class="fa fa-exchange"></i><h4>Platform for material exchange</h4><p>Way to ensure how discarded material of one industry become resource for the other.</p></li><li><i class="fa fa-check"></i><h4>Success stories</h4><p>Inspirational stories implementing waste minimization and  productivity improvement.</p></li><li><i class="fa fa-user"></i><h4>Join plan</h4><p>Offer collaboration and promotional support to independent agencies to work for this cause.</p></div></div></div></div></div></header></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div id="features" class="features-1 padding-top80"><div class="container"><div class="post-heading-center"><h2>Get Started</h2><p>Zero waste based strategies to ensure productivity improvement</p></div><div class="row padding-bottom20"><div class="col-sm-4"><div class="affa-feature-img"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2016/12/feature1.jpg" alt="Image"><h4>Trade Waste</h4><p>We offer an interactive interface that links organizations that have reusable goods they no longer need to those who can use them. This business reuse network helps prevent usable materials from becoming waste and saves users money.</p></div></div><div class="col-sm-4"><div class="affa-feature-img"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2016/12/feature2.jpg" alt="Image"><h4>3 R's-Reuse, Recycle, Reduce</h4><p>We offer simple techniques to recycle, reduce and reuse wastes of different spheres so as to ensure optimum utilisation of wastes.</p></div></div><div class="col-sm-4"><div class="affa-feature-img"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2016/12/initiative.jpg" alt="Image"><h4>Initiatives in this direction</h4><p>We offer instances of various companies who are successfully working in this direction so as to inspire others to join the initiative.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div id="features2" class="features-2"><div class="container"><div class="row padding-bottom20"><div class="col-sm-6 col-md-5 margin-bottom40"><figure><img src="wp-content/uploads/2016/12/apple-devices.jpg" alt="Image"></figure></div><div class="col-sm-6 col-md-7 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-1 margin-bottom20"><div class="col-txt100"><div class="post-heading-left post-heading-top-desc margin-bottom20"><h2>How does this <strong>VPlan</strong> exchange work</h2></div><p>We offer an interactive interface that links organizations that have goods they no longer need to those who can use them effectively.</p><div class="list-icon"><ul><li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o"></i> Receive low- or no-cost materials</li><li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o"></i> Reduce purchase and disposal costs</li><li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o"></i> Free up storage space</li><li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o"></i> Eliminate discharges to land, water or air that are a threat to planetary, human, animal or plant health accounts for free</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="features-3"><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-6 margin-bottom20"><div class="col-txt120"><div class="post-heading-left text-center-sm"><h2><strong>Join Plans.</strong> We'll help you!</h2><p>VPLAN is a support network of people, who realize the need of waste minimization.</p></div><p>Whether you are starting a new program, reviving an old one, or passing off leadership to the incoming class, our coordinators are available for one-on-one program guidance every step of the way.</p><div class="row"><div class="col-sm-6"><div class="affa-col-txt"><h4>Recyclers</h4><p>We want to take recycling beyond just cans and bottles. We’re seeking recycling partners who can help address hard-to-recycle resources like textiles, carpeting, furniture, etc.</p></div></div><div class="col-sm-6"><div class="affa-col-txt"><h4>Upcyclers, and refurbishers</h4><p>Do you fix broken items or turn them into something new and wonderful through upycling? We’d love to connect with you! We’re compiling a database of allies who can help handle waste, from hobbyists to corporations.</p></div></div><div class="col-sm-6"><div class="affa-col-txt"><h4>Preferred Vendor Partnerships</h4><p>VPLAN campus programs seek vendors for truck rental, storage and supplies to ensure waste collection from various industries at economical prices.</p></div></div><div class="col-sm-6"><div class="affa-col-txt"><h4>Customers</h4><p>Great platform for people who wish to get day-to-day utilities well crafted from the discarded wastes they supply us.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-8 col-md-6 col-sm-offset-2 col-md-offset-0"><figure><img src="wp-content/uploads/2016/12/great-support.png" alt="Image" style="padding-top: 120px"></figure></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div id="testimonials" class="bg-grey wrap-container80"><div class="container"><i class="fa fa-quote-left affa-testimonial-icon"></i></div><div class="carousel-slider affa-testimonials-carousel"><div class="slick-slide"><div class="container"><div class="affa-testimonial"><div class="testimonial-txt"><p>"They realize that beauty and hygiene products prevalent throughout homes are often thrown away and contribute to the millions of pounds of garbage and hence their Natural Care Brigade Campaign gives an easy way to send any beauty product containers to Tom’s of Maine for recycling. "</p></div><div class="testimonial-name"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2016/12/testi1.jpg" alt="Avatar"><h4>Tom’s of Maine</h4></div></div></div></div><div class="slick-slide"><div class="container"><div class="affa-testimonial"><div class="testimonial-txt"><p>"They keep their products out of landfills by accepting old technology and recycling the items responsibly. They were the first company to ban e-waste export to developing countries."</p></div><div class="testimonial-name"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2016/12/testi2.png" alt="Avatar"><h4>Dell</h4></div></div></div></div><div class="slick-slide"><div class="container"><div class="affa-testimonial"><div class="testimonial-txt"><p>"Food shelves accept food donations in the form of canned or dry goods, and redistribute it to those who are not able to provide basic food requirements for themselves and/or their families."</p></div><div class="testimonial-name"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2016/12/testi3.jpg" alt="Avatar"><h4>Food to people</h4></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><!-- #counter --><div id="facts" class="bg-img vc_custom_1481038405591"><!-- .bg-overlay --><div class="bg-overlay wrap-container8040"><!-- .container --><div class="container"><!-- .row --><div class="row"><div class="col-sm-3"><div class="affa-counter-txt"><i class="fa fa-globe"></i><h4>2.1B Tons</h4><p>Total</p></div></div><div class="col-sm-3"><div class="affa-counter-txt"><i class="fa fa-paper-plane"></i><h4>34%</h4><p>Paper and Paperboard</p></div></div><div class="col-sm-3"><div class="affa-counter-txt"><i class="fa fa-cutlery"></i><h4>12%</h4><p>Food</p></div></div><div class="col-sm-3"><div class="affa-counter-txt"><i class="fa fa-product-hunt"></i><h4>12%</h4><p>Plastic</p></div></div></div><!-- .row end --></div><!-- .container end --></div><!-- .bg-overlay end --></div><!-- #counter end --></div></div></div></div><div style="clear:both; display: block; overflow: hidden; visibility: hidden; height: 0px;"></div><div id="faq" class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid bg-grey wrap-container80 text-center-xs"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_inner container bootstrap post-heading-center vc_custom_1481041366371"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><h2 style="text-align: center" class="vc_custom_heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2><p style="text-align: center" class="vc_custom_heading">Got questions? We have got the best answers for you.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_inner container bootstrap affa-faq text-center-xs vc_column-gap-30"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><h4 style="text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading">What is the mission of VPLAN?</h4>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p style="text-align: left;">We live in a world with finite resources – to throw them “away” is simply a waste!

Through our network we aim at improving the productivity by employing zero waste technology.We aspire to provide a link between different industries so as to ensure  minimization as well as optimum utilization of waste</p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div></div><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><h4 style="text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading">How do I practice waste management at home?</h4>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p style="text-align: left;">Keep separate containers for dry and wet waste in the kitchen.

Keep two bags for dry waste collection- paper and plastic, for the rest of the household waste.

Keep plastic from the kitchen clean and dry and drop into the dry waste bin. Keep glass /plastic containers rinsed of food matter.
</p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_inner container bootstrap affa-faq vc_column-gap-30"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><h4 style="text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading">What are the rules and regulations guiding waste management in India?
</h4>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p style="text-align: left;">Municipal Solid Waste (Management and Handling) Rules 2000 regulate the management and handling of the municipal solid wastes and are applicable to every municipal authority responsible for collection, segregation, storage, transportation, processing and disposal of municipal solid wastes

E-Waste (Management and Handling) Rules, 2010 regulate the management and handling of electrical and electronic waste and is applicable to every producer, consumer involved in manufacture, sale, purchase and processing of these equipments or its components.</p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div></div><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><h4 style="text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading">What is meant by zero waste?</h4>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p style="text-align: left;">Zero waste means products are designed and used according to the waste reduction hierarchy (prevent waste, reduce and reuse first, then recycle and compost) and the principle of highest and best use, so no material goes to landfill or high-temperature destruction.</p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_inner container bootstrap affa-faq vc_column-gap-30"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><h4 style="text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading">How to prepare compost of our own?</h4>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p style="text-align: left;">You can get an old bin and punch holes around it to help with aeration
.
Dispose off wood chips, saw-dust, yard waste shreds, straw and hay, dry leaves and shredded paper into it.

Now add  grass trimmings, fruit and veggie scraps, green leaves and livestock manure.

Mix and add some water every 7 days. 
In a couple of weeks, the compost will be ready.</p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div></div><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><h4 style="text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading">Why is paper waste not recycled effectively?</h4>
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p style="text-align: left;">The biggest task for paper recycling companies is probably the collection, transporting and sorting of waste paper. This is because we always add paper to other waste items and get them contaminated with food, plastics and metals. Sometimes collected paper is sent back to the landfills because they are too contaminated for use.

 The only solution to it is try to keep waste paper in separate grades at home or in the office.</p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div></div></div><h4 style="text-align: center" class="vc_custom_heading affa-faq-link"><a href="https://twitter.com/envato" target=" _blank" title="envato"><strong>Still have questions? Tweet @vplan for answers!</strong></a></h4></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div id="map" class="affa-map"><a href="#" class="btn-collapse"><i class="fa fa-map-marker"></i></a><div class="map-overlay"><div class="container"><div class="map-heading"><h2>Find Us on the map</h2><p>National Productivity Council of India, 5-6, Lodhi Rd, Gokalpuri, Institutional Area, Lodi Colony, New Delhi, Delhi 110003.</p></div></div></div><div id="companyMap" class="map-frame"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div style="clear:both; display: block; overflow: hidden; visibility: hidden; height: 0px;"></div>

			
